gomodel:SYNGO_5215  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1e: DIXDC1 and PSD95 (DLG4) were enriched in PSD biochemical fractions from P28 mouse brains. 2 distinct isoforms of DIXDC1 can be discerned on the western blot.\n\nFigure 1c: immunofluorescence imaging of DIXDC1 and PSD95 showed partial co-localization in 14DIV cortical neuronal cultures.\n\nFigure 1g: immunofluorescence imaging of GFP-DIXDC1-isoform1 and GFP-DIXDC1-isoform2 together with endogenous PSD95 showed localization of both isoforms to dendrites and dendritic spines in 14DIV cortical neuronal cultures.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Cortical neuron cultures were prepared from Dixdc1 KO mouse, C57BL/6 (Charles River Laboratories), or CD-1 (Charles River) mouse E16 embryos as described previously (Johe et al., 1996).\"\n\nantibody:\ngoat anti-mouse Ccd1/DIXDC1 (dilution, 1:500; R&D systems, AF5599, RRID:AB_2091196)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-03" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5215" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

